entries.femaleVariant: The Mox want to take over Clouds?
Takeover of Lizzie's Bar wasn't exactly smooth.
I'm familiar with the story. Things did not go that smoothly.
I didn't say they did, didn't say they would.
But Evie thought Clouds would be safe. You saw how far that got her... how she ended.
Got the Mox to agree to take over Clouds?
No. I'm tryin' to get you. Know someone at Clouds who'll take our side.
Hey, Judy. How ya feelin'?
What came to you?
You're still in mourning, grief is a process.
Gotta give yourself time to grieve, Judy.
So what'd you come up with?
I'd say I'm on anger. Gonna stay here for a while, too. I can work with anger.
The Mox dive, Lizzie's Bar, used to be a joyhouse. Tyger Claws killed one girl too many, so people took matters into their own hands... Belongs to us, now.
Clouds could stand to get the same makeover.
Will you help?
When're we doin' this?
Early morning, Clouds'll be closed – hardly a soul lurkin' at that time.
Can't be a part of this, Judy. It's just a bad idea.
entries.maleVariant: Can't be part of this, Judy. Just a bad idea.

entries.femaleVariant: Got any better ones?
Shitty. But somethin' came to me.
Experience all its stages, feel 'em, let 'em play out. Shock, anger, depression…
entries.maleVariant: Experience all its stages, feel them, let 'em play out. Shock, anger, depression…

entries.femaleVariant: That's your plan?
Takin' control of Clouds? That's your plan? Feels like you're missing a component or two.
entries.maleVariant: Takin' control of Clouds? That's your plan? Heh, feels like you're missing a component or two.

entries.femaleVariant: Like what?
Like a beginning and a middle. You've got the end, that's all.
entries.maleVariant: Like a beginning and a middle? You've got the end, that's all.

entries.femaleVariant: Middle's in place. Meanin', literally got someone on the inside. And the beginning's you.
Will you help?
Yeah, I'll help.
Can't do this. It's a bad idea.
No.
So you're gonna do nothin'? People are dyin' at Clouds.
People'll die if I help you, too. Sorry.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, people die if I help you, too. Sorry.

entries.femaleVariant: Ugh. Guess no means no.
How early?
Before eight. I'll be by the entrance... Nah, scratch that – the balcony above Clouds.
V... I can't stand by and let things go on like this.
Sure you've thought this through?
Sure you've thought this through, Judy, carefully?
entries.maleVariant: You sure you've thought this through, Judy, carefully?

entries.femaleVariant: Pff, haven't thought it through at all.
All I know's the Mox didn't turn things around by sitting on their tanned and toned asses, doin' nothin'.
OK, so... what's the plan?
First up – we gotta talk to Maiko Maeda. If she's not with us, might as well throw our hands up in the air.
Sure she's gonna wanna help us?
This Maiko – who is she, exactly?
Seem well-connected at Clouds.
Sure Maiko's gonna wanna join forces?
entries.maleVariant: You sure Maiko's gonna wanna join forces?

entries.femaleVariant: If I was sure, I'd be on the holo to her, and we wouldn't be havin' this conversation.
Let me rephrase. Any chance she'll slap us around, then shove us out her megatower window?
entries.maleVariant: Let me rephrase. Is there any chance she'll slap us around, then shove us out her megatower window?

entries.femaleVariant: 'Course, sure.
Guess I can work with that.
How well do you know this Maiko?
Too well.
Evelyn, Maiko... seem to know your way around Clouds.
entries.maleVariant: Evelyn, Maiko... you seem to know your way around Clouds.

entries.femaleVariant: Used to work there. Helped 'em out with their behavioral chip, perfectin' it.
Why'd you leave?
Didn't like the vibe. Place reeked of exploitation.
Maiko Maeda... who is she, exactly?
Girl who unofficially runs Clouds. Good at it, too.
What's she do officially?
She's a doll. So she's a nobody.
Fine. Got me on board.
Woo, yes!
When you wanna meet?
You know Maiko well?
I can't – not right now.
I can't – not right now. Too much shit goin' on as it is.
I get it, V – it's OK. I'm not gonna lie, this'll take a good chunk of time...
But when your hands're free, gimme a shout, all right?
We'll sneak in – no one needs to know we're there.
On the balcony. Got it.
